~ start

Player: I clicked on the locked level.
Player: And then, I couldn't believe what I saw.
Player: What I saw was the weirdest...
Player: The creepiest...
Player: The scariest...

do actor_enter("Lewgend", "open_arms", "center")

Lewgend: DEV INSERT!

do actor_effect("Lewgend", "shock")
do actor_change("Lewgend", "waving")

Lewgend: Hey! I'm Lewgend. How are ya'?
do actor_change("Lewgend", "explaining")
Lewgend: Well, I've got news. Good and bad.


Lewgend: So... bad news first.
do actor_change("Lewgend", "embarrassed")
Lewgend: The demo ends here.
Lewgend: Yeah. I know. Bummer.

do actor_effect("Lewgend", "shock")
do actor_change("Lewgend", "open_arms")

Lewgend: But - good news?
do actor_change("Lewgend", "determined")
Lewgend: Your boy is COOKING.
Lewgend: COOKING so much! I've so much planned for this game!

do actor_change("Lewgend", "explaining")
Lewgend: For example\:
Lewgend: Lemme call our first female love interest... Layla! 
Lewgend: Layla! Get over here would ya'?

# Lewgend slides to the right slot, making room!
do actor_move("Lewgend", "right")

# Layla slides in from off-screen into the left slot!
do actor_dash_in("Layla", "base", "left")
do actor_flip("Layla", true)
Layla: HEY Lew! Called me?
Layla: What's up? How's it going?
Lewgend: Hey! All good, Layla! You seem upbeat today.
Layla: Oh well you know, just trying to keep my spirits up.
Layla: Kinda hard though.. you know? 
Layla: Since you decided to give your protagonist bigger titties than me! 
Lewgend: ..Layla.
Lewgend: Do we really need to do this right now?
Lewgend: We're creating a body positive game! Everybody is built different, you know?
Layla: Whatever. I hope you compensate for this atrocity by giving me a damn good character arc.
Lewgend: Oh you bet! Creating a rich world with interesting characters is the primary goal of this game!
Layla: M'kay.
do actor_flip("Layla", false)
Layla:Anyway, bye now.

# Layla walks off-screen to the left (the way she came in)
do actor_walk_out("Layla", "left")

# Lewgend smoothly slides back to the center of the screen
do actor_move("Lewgend", "center")

Lewgend: Hah. Classic Layla. She really is something.

do actor_flip("Lewgend", true)
Lewgend: But hey! Let's not forget about our first male love interest - Malcolm!
Lewgend: Malcolm, get in here my man.
Malcolm: You sure about that?
Lewgend: Of course! Get that handsome face in here!
#malcolm comes in 
Malcolm: Last time we discussed this, you said I wasn't ready to be shown.
Malcolm: Ever since I've lived my life alone. Devoid of colour and motion.
Lewgend: Well, that's not true! We can still make you move through my sprite operations!
Malcolm: Your sprite wh-?
Lewgend: ZIP!
Lewgend: FLIP!
Lewgend: SLIP!
#malcolm exits
Lewgend: Welp. 
Lewgend: Sorry about that. He still needs a lot of work.


Lewgend: Also—quick note.
Lewgend: All spicy content in the full game is completely optional.
Lewgend: You can enjoy the story however you like.
Lewgend: No pressure.

Lewgend: Now…
Lewgend: Back to reality.

Lewgend: I’m also kind of…
Lewgend: broke.

Lewgend: Making this game solo has been really tough.
Lewgend: I’ve been lucky to work with an amazing freelance artist,
Lewgend: but I don’t have the resources to support them the way this project deserves.

Lewgend: And that’s where you come in.

# shift + patreon icon

Lewgend: If you enjoyed the demo, consider supporting the game on Patreon.
Lewgend: Even $3 a month helps me keep working on this and bringing the full story to life.

Lewgend: Higher tiers will come with some cool extras too—stuff I’m really excited to share.

Lewgend: This game means a lot to me.
Lewgend: It’s something I’ve wanted to make for a long time.

Lewgend: So yeah... if you want to see where this goes -
Lewgend: I’d really, really appreciate your support.

Lewgend: Anyway, that’s my time.
Lewgend: See you soon. Toodles!

Lewgend: And seriously - thanks for playing.


do actor_leave("Lewgend")

=> END
